<title type="html"><![CDATA[Beginner Question. How does SMB1 store levels?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5710&amp;p=52134#p52134"><![CDATA[
There are several layers: <ol style="list-style-type: decimal"><li>background scenery (clouds, hills, fences, trees) </li><li>foreground scenery (8-3 wall, full-screen water) </li><li>terrain patterns (present/absent rows of blocks) </li><li>area data objects (? block here, pipe here, etc) </li></ol><br />One of the area data objects in Y=$C0-$FF changes the foreground scenery; another changes the terrain patterns.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Thu Nov 05, 2009 1:52 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
